<page>
    <shortlink>form layout map properties properties</shortlink>
    <topic>FormView Map Properties Properties</topic>
    <description>Settings for configuring a map control added to the FormView layout.</description>
    <sections>
        <section>
            <title>Alternate HTML</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the HTML to show in place of the map if the latitude/longitude values are blank.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Height</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the map height in pixels.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Latitude</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the field that contains the map latitude value.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Longitude</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the field that contains the map longitude value.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Map class</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the class for the image element that displays the static map.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Map inline style</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the in-line style for the image element that displays the static map.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Map marker color</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the map marker color. The *[ui:Map marker color]* property defines the color to use for the map marker. You can pick from the following list of colors:</p>
            </description>
            <list bullet="true">
                <item>
                    <name>black</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>brown</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>green</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>purple</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>yellow</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>blue</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>gray</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>orange</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>red</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>white</name>
                </item>
            </list>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Map marker size</title>
            <description>
                <p>Defines the map marker size to use. The *[ui:Map marker size]* property defines the size of the map marker. You choose to use the default value or pick an explicit marker size. The following options are available:</p>
            </description>
            <list bullet="true">
                <item>
                    <name>&lt;Default&gt;</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>tiny</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>mid</name>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>small</name>
                </item>
            </list>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Template</title>
            <description>
                <p>Defines a custom template for the map control.</p>
                <p>The *[ui:Template]* property can be used to define a custom layout for the map control separate from the default template for the FormView control.</p>
                <p>For a visual example watch [this video]. To define a default template for all fields on a form view see the '[Default template]' property on the Form Properties tab.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Width</title>
            <description>
                <p>Specify the map width in pixels.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
    </sections>
    <links>
        <link href="https://www.viddler.com/v/5278ed0a">this video</link>
